[9.255, "o", "\r\n"]
[9.555, "o", "8 design decision(s) found:\r\n"]
[9.57, "o", "\r\n"]
[9.585, "o", "  1. [SECURITY-PATTERN] No authentication/authorization layer on patient endpoints handling PHI\r\n"]
[9.6, "o", "     File: src/api/routes/patients.py:13-40\r\n"]
[9.615, "o", "     Alternatives:\r\n"]
[9.63, "o", "       - Add FastAPI Security dependency with JWT or session validation\r\n"]
[9.645, "o", "       - Implement role-based access control (RBAC) decorator\r\n"]
[9.66, "o", "       - Use FastAPI Depends() with custom authorization function\r\n"]
[9.675, "o", "       - Delegate to API gateway for authentication\r\n"]
[9.69, "o", "     Risk: All patient endpoints are publicly accessible. This violates HIPAA (REQ-HIPAA-003) and OWASP requirements. Any unauthenticated user can read, modify, or delete all PHI in the system. Regulatory compliance failure and legal liability.\r\n"]
[9.705, "o", "     ? How should authentication be enforced? Should all endpoints require the same auth level, or do some (e.g., patient self-service) need different rules?\r\n"]
[9.72, "o", "\r\n"]
[9.735, "o", "  2. [SECURITY-PATTERN] Input parameters passed directly to endpoints without Pydantic validation schema\r\n"]
[9.75, "o", "     File: src/api/routes/patients.py:27-34\r\n"]
[9.765, "o", "     Alternatives:\r\n"]
[9.78, "o", "       - Define Pydantic BaseModel for CreatePatientRequest with field validators\r\n"]
[9.795, "o", "       - Use query/body parameters with type hints and Pydantic Field constraints\r\n"]
[9.81, "o", "       - Add manual validation before repository calls\r\n"]
[9.825, "o", "     Risk: No schema validation means invalid data types, missing required fields, or malformed dates reach the database. No sanitization of medical_record_number or other identifiers. Harder to track what formats are expected. No OpenAPI schema generation from request models.\r\n"]
[9.84, "o", "     ? Should date_of_birth be parsed to a date object in the schema, or kept as string? What validation rules (min/max date, format) should be enforced?\r\n"]
[9.855, "o", "\r\n"]
[9.87, "o", "  3. [SECURITY-PATTERN] SQL injection vulnerability in search endpoint with unparameterized query\r\n"]
[9.885, "o", "     File: src/api/routes/patients.py:48-51\r\n"]
[9.9, "o", "     Alternatives:\r\n"]
[9.915, "o", "       - Use SQLAlchemy ORM filter() with parameterized queries\r\n"]
[9.93, "o", "       - Implement whitelist of allowed search fields and use .ilike() with bound parameters\r\n"]
[9.945, "o", "       - Define a SearchPatientRequest schema that maps to safe ORM operations\r\n"]
[9.96, "o", "     Risk: User-supplied `query` string is passed directly to `search_patients()`. If that function constructs raw SQL, attackers can inject SQL commands to exfiltrate data, modify records, or drop tables. OWASP A03:2021 Injection vulnerability.\r\n"]
[9.975, "o", "     ? What does search_patients() do with the query parameter? Should search be limited to specific fields (name, MRN) with exact/prefix matching only?\r\n"]
[9.99, "o", "\r\n"]
[10.005, "o", "  4. [SECURITY-PATTERN] Use of eval() on user-supplied filter expression\r\n"]
[10.02, "o", "     File: src/api/routes/patients.py:54-57\r\n"]
[10.035, "o", "     Alternatives:\r\n"]
